OL,3,CSewage overflows 'not good enough',
OL,4,Cboss of North West water supplier says
OL,6,FUnited Utilities was the latest
OL,7,Fsupplier to face questioning by a
OL,8,Fgroup of MPs on the Environment, Food
OL,9,Fand Rural Affairs Committee.
OL,11,FLast year, the company was accused of
OL,12,Ffailing to report more than 100
OL,13,Fmillion litres of untreated sewage
OL,14,Fthat it illegally discharged into
OL,15,FWindermere over a three-year period.
OL,17,FChief executive Louise Beardmore said
OL,18,Fthat the company needed to rebuild
OL,19,Ftrust in the North West after the
OL,20,Fscandal, and following an increase in
OL,21,Fpollution incidents last year.
